-- Brazil’s First Quarter Economy Climbs 0.2% From Previous Quarter
-- B y   J o s h u a   G o o d m a n
-- 2012-06-01T12:04:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-01/brazil-s-first-quarter-economy-climbs-0-2-from-previous-quarter.html
Brazil ’s economy expanded 0.2 percent
in the first quarter from the previous quarter, the
national statistics agency said today in Rio de Janeiro.  Gross domestic product grew 0.8 percent from a year
earlier.  Analysts had forecast year-on-year expansion of 1.3 percent
and growth of 0.5 percent compared with the fourth quarter,
according to the median estimates from economists surveyed by
Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
